						<div class="col">
							<h4>Energy requirements</h4>
							<p>It is estimated that 556 kWh of electricity is required by the NE H2 process to remove and store 1 t CO2. A 500 MW renewable energy power plant dedicated to NE H2 could therefore consume and store nearly 8 million tonnes of CO2 per day while generating a little more than 2 million kWh in the form of H2. </p>
